#-Function--lockfile
  Function: lockfile
      Desc: return name of current lock file in lockfiles() stack,
          : and optionally add a new lockfile.
          : default is one day. if you are using the .lockfile system,
          : you may wish to set this very differently
  Synopsis: lockfile [newlockfile]
   Example: lck=$(lockfile)
    Source: /usr/share/okusi/entities/entities.d/files/dev/lockfiles/lockfiles.bash
#-Function--lockfile----------------------------------------------------------
